{"id": "duc04-testb-26:10#30", "contents": "De Klerk has stated that when he learned about the bombings, Vlok and Van der Merwe were already in the process of applying for amnesty. He did not think it was necessary to report the matter, as they had already taken steps to seek forgiveness for their actions. This decision was likely influenced by the fact that the amnesty process was designed to promote reconciliation and forgiveness in the aftermath of apartheid-era violence."}
